# Push after changes

After completing code or data changes in this project, **always commit and push to `origin/master`** before finishing the task (unless the user explicitly says not to push).

Workflow:

1. Run `npm run build:only` (see `build-after-changes.mdc`).
2. `git add` relevant files (not secrets).
3. Commit with a concise message focused on why.
4. `git push origin master`

Do not force-push unless the user explicitly requests it.
Do not push if there are no changes to commit.
